quotas.name: Haryana Private Seats - All
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Private Seats - All**

Any one of the below

1) Passed XII in Haryana

2) Children / Wards(if parents are not living)/Dependents of 

    1. regular employees of Haryana State posted in or outside Haryana or on deputation
    2. regular employees of Corp or statutory bodies established by or under an act of the State of Haryana and posted in CG or Haryana or outside Haryana
    3. regulat employees of Govt of India posted in Haryana

3) Children/wards (if parents not living)/dependents of persons who after retirement have permanently settled in Haryana and draw their pensions from the treasuries situated in the State of Haryana

4) Children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of pensioners of Haryana Government irrespective of the fact that the original home of the retiree is in a state other than Haryana or he has settled after retirement in or outside Haryana;

5) Children/Wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of persons, who have permanent home in Haryana and include persons who have been residing in Haryana for a period of not less than 15 years or who have permanent home in Haryana but on account of their occupation they are living outside Haryana;

6) The wives of such persons who are bonafide residents of Haryana irrespective of the fact that they had belonged to any other State before marriage;

7) Persons who were born in Haryana  provided that the parents/guardians (if parents are not living) are:

   1. Citizen of India;
   2. Produce an affidavit to the effect that they or their children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents have not obtained the benefit of Resident in any other State.

8) Children and wards of the accredited journalists residing at Chandigarh and recognized by Government of Haryana

---

quotas.name: Haryana Private Seats - NRI
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Private Seats - NRI**  

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>     
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>     
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>  
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.                     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.    
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.           
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

    2. regular employees of Corp or statutory bodies established by or under an act of the State of Haryana and posted in CG or Haryana or outside Haryana 
    3. regular employees of Govt of India posted in Haryana 
3. Children/wards (if parents not living)/dependents of persons who after retirement have permanently settled
in Haryana and draw their pensions from the treasuries situated in the State of Haryana
4. Children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of pensioners of Haryana Government irrespective of the fact that the original home of the retiree is in a state other than Haryana or he has settled after retirement
in or outside Haryana;
5. Children/Wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of persons, who have permanent home in Haryana and
include persons who have been residing in Haryana for a period of not less than 15 years or who have permanent home in Haryana but on account of their occupation they are living outside Haryana;

    a) Citizen of India.   
    b) Produce an affidavit to the effect that they or their children/wards (if parents are notliving)/dependents have not obtained the benefit of Resident in any other State.

quota.name: Haryana Govt Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - NRI**   

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>    
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>    
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.        
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.       
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.name: Haryana Govt Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - NRI**   

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>    
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>    
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.        
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.       
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.        
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.

f) Such person should be NRI.

list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - All**  
Any one of the below
1. Passed XII in Haryana
2. Children / Wards(if parents are not living)/Dependants of

    1. regular employees of Haryana State posted in or outside Haryana or on deputation
    2. regular employees of Corp or statutory bodies established by or under an act of the State of Haryana and posted in CG or Haryana or outside Haryana 
    3. regular employees of Govt of India posted in Haryana 
3. Children/wards (if parents not living)/dependents of persons who after retirement have permanently settled
in Haryana and draw their pensions from the treasuries situated in the State of Haryana
4. Children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of pensioners of Haryana Government irrespective of the fact that the original home of the retiree is in a state other than Haryana or he has settled after retirement
in or outside Haryana;
5. Children/Wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of persons, who have permanent home in Haryana and
include persons who have been residing in Haryana for a period of not less than 15 years or who have permanent home in Haryana but on account of their occupation they are living outside Haryana;
6. The wives of such persons who are bonafide residents of Haryana irrespective of the fact that they had
belonged to any other State before marriage;
7. Persons who were born in Haryana  provided that the
parents/guardians (if parents are not living) are:

    a) Citizen of India.   
    b) Produce an affidavit to the effect that they or their children/wards (if parents are notliving)/dependents have not obtained the benefit of Resident in any other State.
8. Children and wards of the accredited journalists residing at Chandigarh and recognized by Government of Haryana

Any one of the below1. Passed XII in Haryana2. Children / Wards(if parents are not living)/Dependants of


1. regular employees of Haryana State posted in or outside Haryana or on deputation2. regular employees of Corp or statutory bodies established by or under an act of the State of Haryana and posted in CG or Haryana or outside Haryana 3. regular employees of Govt of India posted in Haryana

  1. Children/wards (if parents not living)/dependents of persons who after retirement have permanently settledin Haryana and draw their pensions from the treasuries situated in the State of Haryana

  2. Children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of pensioners of Haryana Government irrespective of the fact that the original home of the retiree is in a state other than Haryana or he has settled after retirementin or outside Haryana;

  3. Children/Wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of persons, who have permanent home in Haryana andinclude persons who have been residing in Haryana for a period of not less than 15 years or who have permanent home in Haryana but on account of their occupation they are living outside Haryana;

  4. The wives of such persons who are bonafide residents of Haryana irrespective of the fact that they hadbelonged to any other State before marriage;

  5. Persons who were born in Haryana provided that theparents/guardians (if parents are not living) are:


    a) Citizen of India.
    b) Produce an affidavit to the effect that they or their children/wards (if parents are notliving)/dependents have not obtained the benefit of Resident in any other State.



  6. Children and wards of the accredited journalists residing at Chandigarh and recognized by Government of Haryana

quota.name: Haryana Govt Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - NRI**   

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>    
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>    
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.        
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.       
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.name: Haryana Private Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Private Seats - NRI**  

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>     
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>     
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>  
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.                     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.    
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.           
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Private Seats - NRI**  

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>     
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>     
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>  
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.                     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.    
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.           
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

f) Such person should be NRI.
NRI-7

quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Private Seats - All**

Any one of the below

1) Passed XII in Haryana

2) Children / Wards(if parents are not living)/Dependents of 

    1. regular employees of Haryana State posted in or outside Haryana or on deputation
    2. regular employees of Corp or statutory bodies established by or under an act of the State of Haryana and posted in CG or Haryana or outside Haryana
    3. regulat employees of Govt of India posted in Haryana

3) Children/wards (if parents not living)/dependents of persons who after retirement have permanently settled in Haryana and draw their pensions from the treasuries situated in the State of Haryana

4) Children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of pensioners of Haryana Government irrespective of the fact that the original home of the retiree is in a state other than Haryana or he has settled after retirement in or outside Haryana;

5) Children/Wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of persons, who have permanent home in Haryana and include persons who have been residing in Haryana for a period of not less than 15 years or who have permanent home in Haryana but on account of their occupation they are living outside Haryana;

6) The wives of such persons who are bonafide residents of Haryana irrespective of the fact that they had belonged to any other State before marriage;

7) Persons who were born in Haryana  provided that the parents/guardians (if parents are not living) are:

   1. Citizen of India;
   2. Produce an affidavit to the effect that they or their children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents have not obtained the benefit of Resident in any other State.

8) Children and wards of the accredited journalists residing at Chandigarh and recognized by Government of Haryana

quota.name: Haryana Private Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Private Seats - NRI**  

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>     
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>     
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>  
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.                     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.    
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.           
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.name: Haryana Govt Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - NRI**   

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>    
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>    
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.        
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.       
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.name: Haryana Govt Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - NRI**   

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>    
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>    
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.        
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.       
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

Any one of the below
1. Passed XII in Haryana
2. Children / Wards(if parents are not living)/Dependants of

    1. regular employees of Haryana State posted in or outside Haryana or on deputation
    2. regular employees of Corp or statutory bodies established by or under an act of the State of Haryana and posted in CG or Haryana or outside Haryana 
    3. regular employees of Govt of India posted in Haryana 
3. Children/wards (if parents not living)/dependents of persons who after retirement have permanently settled
in Haryana and draw their pensions from the treasuries situated in the State of Haryana
4. Children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of pensioners of Haryana Government irrespective of the fact that the original home of the retiree is in a state other than Haryana or he has settled after retirement
in or outside Haryana;
5. Children/Wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of persons, who have permanent home in Haryana and
include persons who have been residing in Haryana for a period of not less than 15 years or who have permanent home in Haryana but on account of their occupation they are living outside Haryana;
6. The wives of such persons who are bonafide residents of Haryana irrespective of the fact that they had
belonged to any other State before marriage;
7. Persons who were born in Haryana  provided that the
parents/guardians (if parents are not living) are:

    a) Citizen of India.   
    b) Produce an affidavit to the effect that they or their children/wards (if parents are notliving)/dependents have not obtained the benefit of Resident in any other State.
8. Children and wards of the accredited journalists residing at Chandigarh and recognized by Government of Haryana

quota.name: Haryana Govt Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - NRI**   

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>    
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>    
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.        
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.       
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.name: Haryana Govt Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - NRI**   

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>    
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>    
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.        
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.       
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.name: Haryana Govt Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - NRI**   

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>    
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>    
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.        
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.       
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.name: Haryana Private Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Private Seats - NRI**  

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>     
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>     
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>  
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.                     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.    
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.           
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.name: Haryana Private Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Private Seats - NRI**  

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>     
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>     
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>  
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.                     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.    
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.           
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.name: Haryana Private Seats - All
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Private Seats - All**

Any one of the below

1) Passed XII in Haryana

2) Children / Wards(if parents are not living)/Dependents of 

    1. regular employees of Haryana State posted in or outside Haryana or on deputation
    2. regular employees of Corp or statutory bodies established by or under an act of the State of Haryana and posted in CG or Haryana or outside Haryana
    3. regulat employees of Govt of India posted in Haryana

3) Children/wards (if parents not living)/dependents of persons who after retirement have permanently settled in Haryana and draw their pensions from the treasuries situated in the State of Haryana

4) Children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of pensioners of Haryana Government irrespective of the fact that the original home of the retiree is in a state other than Haryana or he has settled after retirement in or outside Haryana;

5) Children/Wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of persons, who have permanent home in Haryana and include persons who have been residing in Haryana for a period of not less than 15 years or who have permanent home in Haryana but on account of their occupation they are living outside Haryana;

6) The wives of such persons who are bonafide residents of Haryana irrespective of the fact that they had belonged to any other State before marriage;

7) Persons who were born in Haryana  provided that the parents/guardians (if parents are not living) are:

   1. Citizen of India;
   2. Produce an affidavit to the effect that they or their children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents have not obtained the benefit of Resident in any other State.

8) Children and wards of the accredited journalists residing at Chandigarh and recognized by Government of Haryana

Any one of the below1. Passed XII in Haryana2. Children / Wards(if parents are not living)/Dependants of


1. regular employees of Haryana State posted in or outside Haryana or on deputation2. regular employees of Corp or statutory bodies established by or under an act of the State of Haryana and posted in CG or Haryana or outside Haryana 3. regular employees of Govt of India posted in Haryana

  1. Children/wards (if parents not living)/dependents of persons who after retirement have permanently settledin Haryana and draw their pensions from the treasuries situated in the State of Haryana

  2. Children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of pensioners of Haryana Government irrespective of the fact that the original home of the retiree is in a state other than Haryana or he has settled after retirementin or outside Haryana;

  3. Children/Wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of persons, who have permanent home in Haryana andinclude persons who have been residing in Haryana for a period of not less than 15 years or who have permanent home in Haryana but on account of their occupation they are living outside Haryana;

  4. The wives of such persons who are bonafide residents of Haryana irrespective of the fact that they hadbelonged to any other State before marriage;

  5. Persons who were born in Haryana provided that theparents/guardians (if parents are not living) are:


    a) Citizen of India.
    b) Produce an affidavit to the effect that they or their children/wards (if parents are notliving)/dependents have not obtained the benefit of Resident in any other State.



  6. Children and wards of the accredited journalists residing at Chandigarh and recognized by Government of Haryana

quota.name: Haryana Private Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Private Seats - NRI**  

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>     
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>    
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>     
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>  
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.                     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.    
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.           
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

quota.name: Haryana Govt Seats - NRI
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - NRI**   

<u>**NRI-1**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs candidates who originally belonged to the State of Haryana    
<u>**NRI-2**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to Haryana State.    
<u>**NRI-3**</u>    
Actual NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union Territories
other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-4**</u>   
Children of NRIs/OCIs/PIOs who originally belonged to an Indian State and Union
Territories other than Haryana.     
<u>**NRI-5**</u>    
Real brother and sister of the candidate.   
<u>**NRI-6**</u>    
a) Real Brother and sister of father i.e. real uncle and real aunt.     
b) Real brother and Sister of mother i.e. real maternal uncle and maternal aunt.        
c) Father and mother of father i.e. grand father and grandmother.       
d) Father and mother of mother i.e. maternal grandfather and maternal grandmother.  
e) First degree-paternal and maternal cousins.  
f) Such person should be NRI.   
<u>**NRI-7**</u>    
Foreign Nationals shall be considered for admission under NRI quota after exhausting the
list of NRIs/ PIOs/OCIs.

NRI-4

quota.name: Haryana Govt Seats - All
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Haryana Govt Seats - All**  
Any one of the below
1. Passed XII in Haryana
2. Children / Wards(if parents are not living)/Dependants of

    1. regular employees of Haryana State posted in or outside Haryana or on deputation
    2. regular employees of Corp or statutory bodies established by or under an act of the State of Haryana and posted in CG or Haryana or outside Haryana 
    3. regular employees of Govt of India posted in Haryana 
3. Children/wards (if parents not living)/dependents of persons who after retirement have permanently settled
in Haryana and draw their pensions from the treasuries situated in the State of Haryana
4. Children/wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of pensioners of Haryana Government irrespective of the fact that the original home of the retiree is in a state other than Haryana or he has settled after retirement
in or outside Haryana;
5. Children/Wards (if parents are not living)/dependents of persons, who have permanent home in Haryana and
include persons who have been residing in Haryana for a period of not less than 15 years or who have permanent home in Haryana but on account of their occupation they are living outside Haryana;
6. The wives of such persons who are bonafide residents of Haryana irrespective of the fact that they had
belonged to any other State before marriage;
7. Persons who were born in Haryana  provided that the
parents/guardians (if parents are not living) are:

    a) Citizen of India.   
    b) Produce an affidavit to the effect that they or their children/wards (if parents are notliving)/dependents have not obtained the benefit of Resident in any other State.
8. Children and wards of the accredited journalists residing at Chandigarh and recognized by Government of Haryana
